## 2) North-Star UI Direction

### 10 Principles

| # | Principle | Testable? |
|---|-----------|-----------|
| 1 | **One visual language, everywhere** — the dashboard must feel like it belongs to the same brand as the homepage | Hold any two screenshots side-by-side: same type scale, same colour tokens, same card radius, same button hierarchy |
| 2 | **Scan-first payroll clarity** — the UI should be scannable in 3 seconds per screen. The primary number (net pay, total hours, employee count) must be the largest element | Eye-tracking test: user can state the "headline number" within 3 seconds |
| 3 | **Guided compliance, not gatekeeping** — the app should guide users toward correct behaviour with helpers, defaults, and warnings, but never block them with legalese | Every warning includes a "fix it" action. Every required field has a "why this matters" tooltip |
| 4 | **Audit-friendly by default** — every payslip, contract, and leave entry has a timestamp, creator, and "what changed" history | Any generated document can be traced back to its inputs and any edits logged |
| 5 | **Mobile-first, desktop-enhanced** — design for 360px first, then expand for 1280px+. Never design desktop-only features | Every screen must pass a 360×800 visual check before merge |
| 6 | **One primary action per screen** — the single most important thing the user can do on any screen must be visually dominant | Every screen has exactly one `Primary` button. All others are `Secondary` or `Ghost` |
| 7 | **Progressive disclosure** — show the minimum viable info first, let the user drill down. Don't front-load complexity | Settings, advanced deductions, audit logs are one level deeper. The happy path is short |
| 8 | **Warm precision** — the visual tone is warm (SA-inspired earthy tones) but precise (tabular numbers, aligned columns, clear labels). Never cold clinical, never playful | Colour palette uses warm neutrals (not cold grey). Numbers always use `tabular-nums` |
| 9 | **Theme parity** — Light and Dark mode must be equally polished. Not "light mode + dark afterthought" | Screenshots of every screen in both modes must be reviewed before release |
| 10 | **Offline-first resilience** — the app works without internet. Every action queues locally, syncs when online, and shows clear status | "Last synced" indicator visible. All data operations work offline |

### Visual / Interaction Posture

**Why "Warm Precision":**
This app handles money, legal obligations, and people's livelihoods. It must feel **trustworthy** (precision, clear hierarchy, tabular numbers) and **approachable** (warm colours, friendly copy, guided flows). Think: *your best friend who also happens to be an accountant*.

**What changes most:**
1. **Navigation**: From flat side-drawer → structured nav with grouping, active states, and platform-appropriate patterns (sidebar on desktop, bottom tabs on Android)
2. **Density**: From "big empty cards with lots of whitespace" → "information-rich dashboard with purposeful hierarchy"
3. **Component consistency**: From "each page invents its own patterns" → "shared component library with consistent states"
4. **Typography**: From "5 different weight scales" → "one defined scale used everywhere"
5. **Colour**: From "amber + undefined blue + hardcoded greys" → "full semantic token set with SA-inspired accents"

### Light / Dark Mode Posture

| Property | Light Mode | Dark Mode |
|----------|-----------|-----------|
| Background base | Warm off-white `#faf9f7` | Warm near-black `#131110` |
| Surface (cards) | Pure white `#ffffff` | Dark charcoal `#1c1916` |
| Elevation | Shadows (subtle grey) | Lighter surface tint (subtle lift) |
| Text primary | Near-black `#1a1a1a` | Warm cream `#ede8e1` |
| Borders | Cool-grey `#e4e4e7` | Warm dark `#2c2720` |
| Accent (amber) | Saturated `#d97706` | Slightly muted `#c8852e` |

Key rule: **Dark mode is NOT "invert everything."** It uses warm dark tones (SA soil-inspired) with slightly desaturated accents for eye comfort.

### South African Colour Integration

| Role | Token Name | Light Value | Dark Value | SA Inspiration |
|------|-----------|-------------|------------|----------------|
| Brand accent | `--color-brand` | `#c47a1c` | `#c8852e` | SA flag gold — warm, authoritative |
| Success | `--color-success` | `#16a34a` | `#3baa7a` | Natural green — Kruger bushveld |
| Warning | `--color-warning` | `#ea580c` | `#d97706` | Warm amber — highveld sunset |
| Error | `--color-error` | `#dc2626` | `#d95f5f` | Red — kept universal for clarity |
| Info | `--color-info` | `#2563eb` | `#60a5fa` | Blue — SA flag blue, trustworthy |
| Neutral | `--color-neutral-*` | Zinc scale | Warm brown scale | Earth tones — KZN clay |

**Rules:**
- SA colours are **accents**, not backgrounds. Cards stay neutral. Text stays grey-scale.
- Gold accent is used for: primary actions, active states, brand elements, links
- Green is used for: success states, compliance-met indicators, leave balance
- Blue is used for: informational badges, trust signals, linked references
- Never use more than 2 accent colours on one screen

