## 3) Key User Workflows

### Flow 1: Onboard Employer + First Employee
| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Screens** | `/onboarding` → `/employees/new` → `/dashboard` |
| **Required data** | Employer name + address (for payslip header). Employee: name, role, hourly rate, start date, ID number (optional), hours/day |
| **Common errors** | Skipping employer setup → payslip has blank header. Rate below minimum wage entered |
| **Guardrails** | Onboarding is blocking: can't reach dashboard without employer name. Rate field auto-populates NMW, warns if user types below it. ID number format validated (SA 13-digit). "Why do we need this?" tooltips on each field |

### Flow 2: Create / Maintain Employment Contract
| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Screens** | `/contracts` → `/contracts/{id}/edit` → PDF preview → share |
| **Required data** | Employee ref, job title, start date, hours, rate, leave entitlements, notice period, special clauses |
| **Common errors** | Missing signature / acceptance. Outdated rate (didn't update after wage review). Contract not generated at all |
| **Guardrails** | Contract wizard with step-by-step flow. Red "unsigned" badge until employee acceptance recorded. Auto-warns if contract rate differs from latest payslip rate. Contract expiry / renewal reminders |

### Flow 3: Capture Hours / Attendance
| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Screens** | `/wizard` step 1 + step 2 (hours + Sunday/holiday) |
| **Required data** | Pay period dates, ordinary hours, overtime, Sunday hours, public holiday hours, days worked |
| **Common errors** | Entering period that overlaps with an existing payslip. Ordinary hours that don't match days × hours/day. Forgetting public holidays that fall in the period |
| **Guardrails** | Auto-detect public holidays in date range, prompt to apply. Warn if ordinary hours ÷ days worked ≠ expected hours/day. Block overlapping pay periods. 4-hour minimum rule assistant |

### Flow 4: Calculate Pay + Deductions
| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Screens** | `/wizard` step 3 (deductions) + step 4 (review) |
| **Required data** | UIF status (auto from total hours), accommodation deduction toggle, leave taken |
| **Common errors** | Not understanding why UIF applies/doesn't apply. Accommodation deduction exceeding 10% cap. Total deductions leaving net pay below NMW |
| **Guardrails** | UIF explained inline with clear "24-hour rule" callout. Accommodation auto-capped with explanation. Review screen shows full breakdown with highlighted warnings before save. "Net pay below minimum — check your inputs" warning |

### Flow 5: Generate Payslip + Export / Share
| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Screens** | `/preview?payslipId=x` → PDF download / WhatsApp share |
| **Required data** | All wizard data + employer settings |
| **Common errors** | Employer details not set (blank header). PDF generated with wrong period dates. Sharing PII via insecure channel |
| **Guardrails** | Preview screen shows A4 PDF rendering before download action. "Employer details missing" warning with "fix it" link to settings. Share sheet with privacy notice. Watermark on free-tier exports |

### Flow 6: Track Leave + Public Holidays
| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Screens** | `/leave?employeeId=x` |
| **Required data** | Leave type (annual/sick/family), dates, employee ref |
| **Common errors** | Not tracking leave at all (common). Exceeding annual leave entitlement. Not accounting for public holidays |
| **Guardrails** | Dashboard shows leave balance per employee. Warning when leave exceeds BCEA entitlement. Public holiday calendar built in with auto-detection |

### Flow 7: Maintain Records / Audit Trail
| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Screens** | `/employees/{id}/history` → individual payslip detail |
| **Required data** | Historical payslips, contracts, leave records |
| **Common errors** | Deleting records accidentally. No export for dispute resolution |
| **Guardrails** | Soft-delete with recovery period. Full history with timestamps. Export to PDF bundle for CCMA/DOL compliance. "Record retention" info panel (BCEA requires 3 years) |

### Flow 8: Bulk Payroll Run
| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Screens** | Dashboard → "Run monthly payroll" panel |
| **Required data** | Employees with existing payslips to repeat |
| **Common errors** | Running bulk without checking individual changes (rate, hours). Duplicate runs for same period |
| **Guardrails** | Confirmation screen showing each employee + their rate + last month data. Block duplicate periods. Individual override option before bulk save |

