## 4) Information Architecture & Navigation

### Proposed Sitemap

```
├── Home (marketing/landing — public)
├── Onboarding (first-time flow — linear)
│
├── Dashboard (primary workspace)
│   ├── Compliance summary
│   ├── Upcoming actions (pay day, contract renewal, holidays)
│   ├── Quick actions (new payslip, add employee)
│   └── Monthly overview (chart, totals)
│
├── Employees
│   ├── Employee list (filter, search)
│   ├── Employee detail
│   │   ├── Profile (edit)
│   │   ├── Pay history
│   │   ├── Leave tracker
│   │   ├── Contracts
│   │   └── Documents (certificates, disciplinary)
│   └── Add/Edit employee
│
├── Payslip Wizard (step flow)
│   ├── Step 1: Hours & period
│   ├── Step 2: Sunday & holidays
│   ├── Step 3: Deductions & leave
│   └── Step 4: Review & confirm
│
├── Preview & Export
│
├── Tools
│   ├── NMW Calculator (quick calc, no save)
│   ├── uFiling export
│   └── Compliance guide (rules reference)
│
├── Settings
│   ├── Employer profile
│   ├── Pay rules (BCEA defaults)
│   ├── Backup & Sync
│   └── Appearance (theme, mode)
│
└── Legal (terms, privacy, refund)
```

### Navigation Model

#### Desktop Web: **Fixed left sidebar**
- **Why**: Payroll apps are workspace tools. Users spend 5–20 minutes per session, visiting multiple sections. A persistent sidebar provides constant orientation and zero-click navigation.
- **Width**: 240px collapsed to 64px (icon-only) for focus mode
- **Sections**: Grouped as: **Work** (Dashboard, Employees, Payslip, Preview), **Tools** (Calculator, uFiling, Rules), **Admin** (Settings, Legal)
- **Active state**: Amber left-bar indicator + filled icon + bold text
- **Footer**: "Support" link + theme toggle + version

#### Android App: **Bottom navigation (4 items) + drawer for extras**
- **Bottom tabs**: Dashboard | Employees | New Payslip | More
- **Why**: Bottom tabs are thumb-reachable, fit the 4-item sweet spot, and match Android Material 3 patterns
- **"More" tab**: Opens a settings/tools drawer (calculator, rules, uFiling, settings, legal)
- **FAB (Floating Action Button)**: Not used on bottom bar screens — instead, the primary CTA lives inline (e.g., "Add Employee" button at top of list, "Generate Payslip" at bottom of wizard)

#### Mobile Web (< 768px):
- **Hamburger + sliding drawer** (current pattern, but improved with grouping + active state)
- **Bottom sticky action bar**: On wizard screens, the Next/Back buttons are in a fixed bottom bar for thumb reach

#### Thumb Reach & Safe Areas
- All primary actions in bottom 60% of android viewport
- Bottom nav bar height: 80px (includes safe area inset)
- Minimum tap target: 48×48dp (Android), 44×44px (web)
- No interactive elements within 16px of edges on mobile

### Naming Conventions
| Internal jargon | User-facing label |
|----------------|------------------|
| Payslip wizard | Create Payslip (step 1 of 4) |
| Employee detail | [Employee Name] — Profile |
| Pay history | Pay History |
| uFiling export | eFiling Export |
| NMW Calculator | Wage Calculator |
| BCEA settings | Pay Rules |
| Pro Status | Your Plan |

