## 8) Implementation Roadmap

### Phase 0: Foundation (Week 1) — "The skeleton"
| What ships | Why first |
|-----------|-----------|
| Design tokens in CSS (full colour set, typography scale, spacing, radii) | Everything else depends on this |
| [globals.css](file:///c:/Users/mzaka.ZAK-PC/Documents/Apps/LekkerLedger-1/src/app/globals.css) overhaul with light/dark token sets | Fixes the `--blue-500` blocker + theme foundation |
| Typography scale applied to all headings/body | Immediate visual consistency win |
| Shared `PageHeader`, `PageShell`, `StickyBottomBar` layout components | Structural consistency for all pages |

**Done when**: Every page uses the same tokens. Typography looks consistent across all screens. Light and dark mode both render correctly with no hardcoded colours.

### Phase 1: Navigation & Shell (Week 2) — "Know where you are"
| What ships | Why second |
|-----------|-----------|
| Sidebar with active state, grouping, collapse (desktop) | Biggest orientation win |
| Bottom nav for Android / mobile web | Platform-appropriate navigation |
| Side drawer dark mode logo fix | Broken state fix |
| Breadcrumbs on detail pages | Orientation for deep pages |

**Done when**: User can navigate to any screen and always know where they are. Active state visible. Dark mode logo correct.

### Phase 2: Core Screens (Weeks 3–4) — "The daily work"
| What ships | Why third |
|-----------|-----------|
| Dashboard overhaul (compliance bar, stat cards, employee quick list) | First screen users see after onboarding |
| Employee list → detail migration (table on desktop, cards on mobile) | Second most visited screen |
| Employee action buttons consolidated (primary + overflow menu) | Fixes button overflow |
| Payslip history view with filters | Critical for audit trail |

**Done when**: Dashboard shows compliance status + stats + employee list. Employee page has clean action layout. History is filterable.

### Phase 3: Wizard & Preview (Week 5) — "The core flow"
| What ships | Why fourth |
|-----------|-----------|
| Wizard sticky bottom bar + stepper refinement | Fixes thumb reach |
| Review step with compliance checklist | Prevents mistakes |
| Preview screen with A4 rendering + share sheet | Export quality |
| Guardrail validation patterns | Legal compliance |

**Done when**: Full happy path (create employee → wizard → preview → export) works at 360×800 with no layout issues, all compliance guardrails active.

### Phase 4: Polish & Extras (Week 6) — "Premium feel"
| What ships | Why last |
|-----------|---------|
| Motion system (animations, transitions, loading states) | Polish layer |
| Empty states with illustrations | First-time experience |
| Offline indicator + sync status | Resilience |
| WhatsApp share integration | User request |
| Accessibility audit + fixes | Compliance |

**Done when**: App passes contrast checks, animation feels smooth, offline mode works, WhatsApp sharing generates correct PDF.

### Risk Register

| # | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|------|-----------|--------|------------|
| 1 | Token migration breaks existing styles | High | High | Phase 0 does tokens ONLY. Visual regression screenshots before/after. |
| 2 | Navigation change confuses existing users | Medium | Medium | Phase 1 keeps all existing routes. Only adds nav chrome around them. |
| 3 | Dashboard overhaul takes too long | Medium | Low | MVP dashboard = compliance bar + employee list. Chart/stats are P2. |
| 4 | Dark mode regressions | High | Medium | Automated screenshot comparison in both themes after every phase. |
| 5 | Wizard guardrails create friction | Low | High | All guardrails are warnings by default, not blocks (except NMW). User testing. |
| 6 | Android TWA doesn't pick up web changes | Low | Low | TWA wraps the PWA — web changes propagate. Test after each phase. |
| 7 | Performance regression from new components | Low | Medium | Bundle size checks. Lazy load non-critical components (charts, PDF preview). |
| 8 | Scope creep (new features disguised as "UI fixes") | High | High | Strict rule: no new features in Phase 0–3. Phase 4 extras are explicitly scoped. |

### Theme Rollout Plan
1. **Phase 0**: Define all tokens in CSS variables. Apply to `body`, `Card`, `Button`, `Input` only.
2. **Phase 1**: Migrate navigation components to token system.
3. **Phase 2–3**: Migrate all remaining screens. After each screen: capture light + dark screenshots, compare.
4. **Phase 4**: Final audit — every component in both themes, contrast checked.
5. **Ongoing**: CI check — any PR that introduces a hardcoded colour value (`#xxx`, `rgb(...)`) outside [globals.css](file:///c:/Users/mzaka.ZAK-PC/Documents/Apps/LekkerLedger-1/src/app/globals.css) fails lint.

### Parallel Run Strategy
- **No feature flags needed**: Changes are CSS/component-level, not route-level. Old and new can't coexist meaningfully.
- **Route-by-route**: Each page migrated independently. Navigation changes are global (Phase 1) but backward-compatible (all routes stay the same).
- **Rollback**: Git branch per phase. If Phase N breaks something, revert that branch only.

